title: Ask HN: Roast My Landing Page
text:
Hi HN,

We often get a bad rap for being too critical of newly formed projects. However, I think this is actually a strength of ours. There is always going to be the dropbox or airbnb that we completely miss, but for 99% of other startups, I think our tendency to give ruthless feedback is actually net helpful.

In that vein, I'd like to invite HN to roast the landing page of my newest project. My co-founder and I did spend a lot of time on it, but that's no reason to go easy on us.

Let it rip!

https://beamanalytics.io/

Ask HN: Which products you find best designed from UI/UX perspective?
text:
I like below applications from UI/UX perspective 
1. Canva.com -- Really makes designing graphics pretty easy and has a easy to use, intuitive UI
2. Trading view -- Shows the data heavy application in an easy way. No wonder it has become the go-to application for traders.      
Also what is final goal of UI/UX ? How would you measure UI/UX of an application.  Is it to look good ? Is it to have all the features ? Is it to help customer get the "intended" job done as quickly and efficiently as possible? Is it to be communicative ?
